 <text>
  <front>
   <head>Written for my Son, upon Lady Santry's coming to School, to see her Son, and getting the Scholars a Play-Day.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">, lovely and divine,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Eager to see her ,</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Blessing the Nations as she pass'd,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Reach'd the fell Tyrant's Court at last;</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Around her shot a Gleam of Light,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Diffusing Joy, dispelling Night;</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And, whilst she gilds the dismal Gloom,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The Damn'd a-while forget their Doom;</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The  no longer fill;</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And  Stone stood still;</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">wonders why he strove,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">With impious Arts, to rival ;</l>
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Grim  smil'd; all Hell look'd gay;</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Happy, as we were Yesterday.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
